                            <comment id="13276771" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Wed, 16 May 2012 14:45:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Give me a bit and I&apos;ll try and offer a simple cmd to get two collections up.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13276859" author="steffkes" created="Wed, 16 May 2012 16:28:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Mark, perhaps that&apos;s another bug, but perhaps this command demonstrates what you wanted to show?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;java -DzkRun -Dcollection.configName=myconf -Dbootstrap_confdir=./solr/conf -Dsolr.solr.home=multicore -jar start.jar&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this results in the following clusterstate.json:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;{
