        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;shard&quot;&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;shard1&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;leader&quot;&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;state&quot;&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;active&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;core&quot;&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;core1&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;collection&quot;&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;core1&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;node_name&quot;&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;debian2:8983_solr&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;base_url&quot;&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;http:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//debian2:8983/solr&quot;&lt;/span&gt;}}},
&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;core0&quot;&lt;/span&gt;:{&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;shard1&quot;&lt;/span&gt;:{&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;debian2:8983_solr_core0&quot;&lt;/span&gt;:{
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;shard&quot;&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;shard1&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;leader&quot;&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;state&quot;&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;active&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;core&quot;&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;core0&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;collection&quot;&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;core0&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;node_name&quot;&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;debian2:8983_solr&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;base_url&quot;&lt;/span&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;http:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//debian2:8983/solr&quot;&lt;/span&gt;}}}}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but only &lt;b&gt;core0&lt;/b&gt; is visible for the Graph-Views.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If so, how would we like to display this? Otherwise, ignore this comment ;&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13276863" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Wed, 16 May 2012 16:36:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, that is it exactly. It would be nice if the view for each collection was simply stacked on top of each other - that is, the first would be as it is now, and the next below it and so on. Then you can just scroll down and see the view for each collection?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13276886" author="steffkes" created="Wed, 16 May 2012 17:00:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;i&apos;m not sure, that&apos;s the reason why i&apos;m asking. While thinking about this ... perhaps it&apos;s a bit more like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;core0 \
       - shard1 - debian2
core1 /&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Because it&apos;s running the same shard on the same machine. If we have core0 on debian2 and core1 on debian3, then like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;core0 - shard1 - debian2

core1 - shard1 - debian3&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(regardless if that configuration would make sense or not, just for demonstration)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;in either case, that would mean, that (at least) for the radial view, we could have a graph with multiple root-nodes. don&apos;t know why i&apos;ve included that strict handling for one collection :/&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13276945" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Wed, 16 May 2012 18:03:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;shard1 can be anything though - its just a shard&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/thumbs_down.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; name by default. So just as often, there would be no overlap in shard name for the different collections. I think logically they should be presented as separate trees.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13276979" author="steffkes" created="Wed, 16 May 2012 18:29:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yepp, of course .. just an idea &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; I&apos;ll try to bring up an patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
